<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 12:25PM CDT  by NWS Kansas City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Randolph and
southeastern Macon Counties through 1245 PM CDT...
At 1225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Cairo, or 8 miles south of Macon, moving northeast at
70 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Moberly, Macon, Clark, Cairo, Renick, Jacksonville and Excello.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for north central
Missouri.</instruction>
